I've ordered from Silvana before and would probably give their food 2 or 3-stars. Their chicken shwarma and falafel were not bad, and their za'atar pita chips are actually quite good if you're lucky and they hold up during delivery (I've gotten them crispy, and I've gotten them soggy). Still can't really hold a candle to other falafel spots like Hummus Kitchen and Taim.  However, I'm giving this place 1 star because of their obnoxiously loud music now that outdoor dining has reopened. I live a block away, have double paned windows, and Silvana is blasting music (with a DJ) until 11pm or 12am :(  I have no problem with live music, but this is a little ridiculous... 3 weeks in a row...

Honestly I had super high hopes for this place. I have heard it mentioned a number of times. Friends visit regularly. But when I went, I was not super impressed. Yet the volume is so load not only can you not hear your party, the venue should offer earplugs. We had to make our own from napkins.  The food is Israeli style and none of what I tried blew me away. Infact most was mediocre at best. There are so many more options for this type of food that it's just not worth it.  Drinks here are alright and expensive. But they do give you a free one if it's your birthday 🤷‍♂️... Does that make it worth it? Probably not.  I'll maybe have to give them another shot but I won't be going out of my way for that.

We leave in the neighborhood. We went for lunch there with my mother and my son a few weeks ago. When time came to pay the bill, I went to the register where the lady there gave me a credit card receipt with a total but she did not give me the list of items/dishes with the individual prices. The total seemed higher than what I had expected, I asked but I was somehow bamboozled. I thought that I was confused so I paid, with a tip included.  In my way home, I re did the math and realized that I had been overcharged. I told my husband, and he said that had happened to him too when he went there with a colleague for lunch. Too much of a coincidence. Beware!!! Cheating customers seems to be a common practice there. Ask for your detailed receipt!

One of those little Gems in HARLEM!  I was in the mood for Indian, middle east or African food and found this place on Google Maps.  Instead of taking the 1 Train i accidentally took the 2 train and walked 116 nearly end to end.  I was EXHAUSTED but enjoyed myself walking through the streets Harlem which i dont get to do often.  Coming in you noticed the decor which most of it is for sale.  Decor with the natural light really hit the mark for me. Amazing colors and textures everywhere.  Music in the background was a nice touch and very subtle.   Classic Reggae played which i went in on my Chicken, veggies, potatoes and Summer ALE.  Forgive me.. i dont remember the name of the chicken plate and asked the server to recommend a side for me. i said.."I trust you".. and she brought back fried potato's.  I was very impressed with all and all was well priced.  About $20-22 with a beer.  I even stayed for a CHAI.   I WOULD highly recommend this lil bistro.  oh.. one more thing. They have a speakeasy downstairs with Moroccan-style tables and stools according to the website.  So.. you know i will be back.  :)   Thank you HARLEM!

Pro-tip: The chicken shwarma is ALWAYS a winner.
